<font class="print-title">N.A.T.O. to Close Membership</font><br />
<font class="print-sub">Date: Friday, February 14 @ 01:12:40<br />
Topic News</font>
<br /><br />
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal">As you all know, there is a vote running regarding how many member guilds N.A.T.O. should comprise of.  This issue was never really discussed in any great detail when N.A.T.O. was first formed.  Due to our recent explosion of new members, though, the time has finally come to settle this issue.  There has also been much debate in the Message Forums and online regarding this question.  So, how many members should N.A.T.O. have?<br />
<br />
Currently, 10 is the leader in the Polls, with 15 being just ONE VOTE behind!  CAST YOUR VOTE NOW!  I will close this poll on Sunday (Monday for me) and the winner shall be the limit.<br />
<br />
Already have a guild in Applicant Status?  No worries.  All applicants RETURNED prior to the cut-off will receive consideration and be admitted - provided they get the necessary vote from the Alliance Council.  That means that if 10 guilds is the winning vote, we may end up with 13 member guilds.  However, if someone were to leave N.A.T.O. (now, why would you want to do that???), then no new members would be accepted until after the membership dropped below 10 guilds.<br />
<br />
This is a CLOSE race!  Your vote will definately count here!  Do it.  Do it NOW!<br />
<br />
 - X<br />
<br />
</font>
</td></tr>
